Russian YouTuber Alexander Giniyatullin captured the terrifying moment a stream of soil flowed down a bank next to a main road . 
  The eerie phenomenon is called an 'earthflow' and is a rare type of landslide . 
  It happened in the Kemerovo Region of Russia on April 1 . 
  The earthflow crushed trees and left toppled power lines in its wake . 
  Research suggests that rockfalls are caused by warming temperatures . 
 